Classes in alphabetsoup.framework used by alphabetsoup.base
Bucket
          Bucket defines the interface that buckets must implement in order to properly interact within AlphabetSoup.
Bucketbot
          Bucketbot defines the interface that robots (bucketbots) must provide to operate in AlphabetSoup.
Circle
          Class Circle implements a circle in 2D space and functions to determine its relation to other geometric shapes (such as collisions with rectangles and circles)
Letter
          The class Letter makes up wordList for completion It is dispensed by LetterStation, carried in Bucket, and consumed by WordStation
LetterColor
          LetterColor represents the color of a Letter tile.
LetterStation
          LetterStation defines the interface that letter stations must provide to operate in AlphabetSoup.
SimulationWorld
          SimulationWorld is the base class of the AlphabetSoup simulation itself.
Updateable
          Updateable is an interface which should be implemented by any agent in the system.
Word
          The class Word contains Letter objects that make up a word that must be completed.
WordList
          WordList manages the incoming and outgoing Words of AlphabetSoup.
WordStation
          WordStation defines the interface that word stations must provide to operate in AlphabetSoup.
